This paper is about evaluating grammatical error correction models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses various machine learning models, such as LSTM, CNN, and transformer, which are commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates the models' performance on different learner corpora, which involves analyzing large datasets (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the limitations of current evaluation methods and proposes new approaches, which could fall under the category of robotics (cs.RO) or education (cs.EDU).
